main event: A flight of 35 men aboard the aircraft Quants 586 en route from Nandi to Honolulu at 37,000 feet, observed lights of another aircraft moving east at around 35,000 feet. When Quants 586 turned on their landing lights, the other aircraft extinguished all of its lights.
interesting points: The other aircraft was spotted southwest of Canton at 08/1470Z.
Quants 586 checked with Canton radio, and they reported no other traffic in that area besides flight 586.
The weather was clear at the time of the sighting.
The report was forwarded to various military commands.
location: Southwest of Canton, Fiji to Honolulu
